        <body>
            <div type="figure" subtype="drawing">
                <figure>
                <!--<head type="title"><handShift new="#HANDJR1833-34" script="print" medium="pencil"/>Title of Drawing</head>-->
                    <figDesc>Pen and ink, approx. 6.8 &#x00D7; 12.4 cm (image only). The editors of the <ref type="note" subtype="bibliographical" target="library_edition_note.php">Library Edition</ref> 
                        describe the image as &#x201C;a sketch of a wooded, high&#x2010;banked river, with towers and a church in the distance&#x201D; 
                        (<ref type="bibliography" target="bibliography.php#JRWORKSLE">Ruskin, <hi rend="italic">Works</hi></ref>, 2:354n.). 
                        The sketch shows a grouping of <placeName corresp="#ANDERNACH">Andernach</placeName>&#x02BC;s most familiar medieval buildings. 
                        In the sketch, standing closest to the river, is the sixteenth&#x02010;century <placeName type="building" corresp="#ANDERNACHCRANE">crane</placeName>; 
                        in the middle distance, the fifteenth&#x02010;century <placeName type="building" corresp="#ANDERNACHROUNDTOWER">round tower</placeName>; 
                        and in the far distance, the towers of <placeName type="building" corresp="#STMARYASSUMPTIONANDERNACH">St. Mary Assumption Cathedral</placeName>. 
                        In the drawing, <persName corresp="#JR">Ruskin</persName> has crowded these buildings closer together than they can in fact be seen in a single view.
                    </figDesc>
                </figure>
            </div>
        </body>
